The paper focuses on representation learning in the context of reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of variational methods and optimization algorithms, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve training agents to perform tasks in simulated environments, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper includes analysis of the relationship between their method and mutual information neural estimation, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV).
